===Etymology===
From {{etyl|it|en}} {{term|lava||lava|lang=it}}, originally, in Naples, a torrent of rain overflowing the streets, from {{term|lavare||to wash|lang=it}}. See etymology for the English verb {{term|lave|lang=en}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|US}}, {{a|UK}} {{enPR|läʹvə}}, {{IPA|/ˈlɑːvə/|lang=en}}
* {{a|CA}} {{IPA|/ˈlɑːvə/|/ˈlævə/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|ɑːvə|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# The melted [[rock]] ejected by a [[volcano]] from its [[crater]] or [[fissure]]d sides.
# {{context|informal|proscribed|lang=en}} [[magma|Magma]].<!--, molten rock ''within'' the earth-->
# A shade of red, named after the volcanic lava.
#: {{color panel|CF1020}}

====Usage notes====
Geologists make a distinction between [[magma]] (molten rock underground) and [[lava]] (molten rock on the surface).

